//Fracture – Tibia proximal AO 41 - 41A: Extraarticular



Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 - Bones of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Fracture – Tibia proximal AO 41' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And '41A: Extraarticular' radio button is enabled
And '41B: Partial articular' radio button is enabled
And '41C: Articular' radio button is enabled
And 'Fracture prox. tibia, not further specified' radio button is enabled


When I select '41A: Extraarticular' radio button
Then '41A1: Avulsion fracture' radio button is enabled
And '41A2: Metaphyseal, 1-Fragment' radio button is enabled
And '41A3: Metaphyseal, multifragmentary' radio button is enabled

When I select '41A1: Avulsion fracture' radio button
Then '41A1.1: Capsular attachments' radio button is enabled
And '41A1.2: Tuberositas' radio button is enabled
And '41A1.3: Intercondylar eminence' radio button is enabled

When I select '41A1.1: Capsular attachments' radio button
then 'h: Medial' radio button is enabled
And 'n: Lateral (Segond fracture)' radio button is enabled

When I select '41A1.3: Intercondylar eminence' radio button
then 'o: Anterior' radio button is enabled
And 'p: Posterior' radio button is enabled


When I select '41A2: Metaphyseal, 1-Fragment' radio button
Then '41A2.1: Spiral fracture' radio button is enabled
And '41A2.2: Oblique fracture' radio button is enabled
And '41A2.3: Transverse fracture' radio button is enabled


When I select '41A3: Metaphyseal, multifragmentary' radio button
Then '41A3.1: Intact wedge' radio button is enabled
And '41A3.2: Fragmentary wedge' radio button is enabled
And '41A3.3: Multifragmentary' radio button is enabled

When I select '41A3.1: Intact wedge' radio button
then 'f: Lateral' radio button is enabled
And 'h: Medial' radio button is enabled

When I select '41A3.2: Fragmentary wedge' radio button
then 'f: Lateral' radio button is enabled
And 'h: Medial' radio button is enabled
